ion. However,\nselecting a hot sample of clusters yields profiles that evolve significantly\ncloser to the self-similar prediction. In conclusion, our results show that\nunderstanding the selection function is vital for robust calibration of cluster\nproperties with mass and redshift.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 15 Jul 2016 16:15:26 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 15 Nov 2016 09:34:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-12-14"}
